11:26.135 --> 11:55.922
because I feel that that the scientist does have an 
obligation to translate his findings into useful

11:56.138 --> 12:04.106
information for the public. And the public 
includes here anybody that's not a scientist. And

12:09.992 --> 12:13.856
indeed, it includes anybody that's not a 
scientist in his field. And so I have felt that it

12:15.077 --> 12:26.128
was not only, in a sense, an obligation of the 
scientist to provide the basis for the technology

12:26.800 --> 12:48.008
that made products that society wanted, but it was 
also necessary for the scientists to attempt to

12:26.800 --> 12:48.008
find ways to solve the problems of the byproducts 
of these things that were dangerous to the

12:26.800 --> 12:48.008
environment. And so all the way through, I have 
tried not to condemn what industry was doing, say,

12:54.813 --> 13:09.628
to the marine environment so much as to find ways to 
solve the problem to make what they were doing less

12:54.813 --> 13:09.628
